15:
Wow. Your skills of observation are
certainly polished, Meryll.
18:
N-not at all, I just did what came
naturally.
21:
Firm orders and a knowledge of your
allies' respective abilities... You're
more fledgling strategist than
aspiring author.
25:
Ah, which is why I wanted to ask
youâ€”don't you think Alk has been on
the receiving end of a few too many
attacks?
28:
Even with other comrades around,
he prefers to take the defensive.
Though one would assume he's
more naturally suited for
aggression...
32:
Oh my god, I've always thought of
Alk as a top! A t-top fighter!
39:
But, in my opinion, I think it's best not
to worry about who's in front and
who's in back.
54:
Phew... That was close. I almost went
overboard back there.
56:
Pleasure should NOT mix with
business.
58:
But here in Starview Village, there's
way too much imagination fuel!
How do I manage adventuring
without daydreaming?!
63:
I'll just have to get it all out of my
system! With art!
67:
No... That's not how I pictured it in
my head... Sometimes it's hotter
when you DON'T see...
72:
It's no use... Should I cut back a few
of these tropes? But how to make
each scene recognizable?
94:
Ah, I wanted to ask: why did you
write Alk to be stronger than Nimbus?
101:
No! N-n-n-no! We're not having this
conversation!
105:
Oh, thank god! I hadn't gotten to the
saucy stuff yet! We're safe!
118:
N-no means no! Besides, there's
nothing after this part! I was just
applying the finishing touches!
126:
Everyone holds a certain view about
you, Meryll.
131:
That you are talented and
interesting.
135:
That is why I would like to read the
fruits of your labor. If you will let me.
140:
Th-those innocent eyes!
Fine. After I've written something
age-appropriate, I'll share with you.
156:
New Parquet books in stock! And the
latest publication from Merry Sheep
is also available!
166:
I'LL TAKE EVERYTHING YOU HAVE IN
STOCK! EVERY LAST PAGE!
169:
I'm afraid this graphic novel is sold
one per customer. No exceptions.
173: Wait, is this your book, Meryll?
178:
How about that! Congratulations,
Meryll! Why didn't you tell us about
your publishing debut?
183:
You've got it all wrong! I swear, this
isn't mine!
192:
No, no, no! Not you! I didn't writeâ€”
This book wasn't written with
developing minds, erm, in mind!
197:
Don't be so humble. Sure, it is a
rather thin volume, but the binding
is superb and the inner cover
illustration is sublime.
202:
Ah! Why don't I do a little advertising
for you? You could use a spotlight
for your hard work!
207:
Good day, bookseller! This new
publication you have lined up here
is by the one and only Meryll...
212:
OH MY GOD! P-p-please stop! Don't
tell anyone my real name!
216:
Yeah, Light... Maybe you should
respect her wishes...
222:
How to explain... Wouldn't you feel
embarrassed if your secret love
letters were suddenly traced back to
you?
227:
YES! Exactly! I claim my right to
anonymity!
231:
Yeesh. The ways of writers are vast
and unknowable...
